 =C3=97 (d)<sub>2</sub>. Thus, only the final value of the area of the kite=
 will remain a product of (d)<sub>1</sub> and (d)<sub>2</sub>. This means i=
t will double the value of the area of the kite.</p></div></div></div></div=
